Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.10,0:00:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Everyone, Kaleido Star is about to start!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.09,0:00:20.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When watching Kaleido Star,\Nplease keep the room brightly lit,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.82,0:00:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and sit as far from the TV as you can.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.02,0:00:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm Sora Naegino.\NI came to America all by myself{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.20,0:00:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}with aspirations of joining Kaleido Stage.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.25,0:00:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Everything is new to me, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.02,0:00:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but I'm doing my best in the spirit\Nof "try it rather than think about it."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.68,0:00:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's nothing I can't do if I try,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.93,0:00:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and if I can do it without\Ntrying, that'll be super lucky.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.73,0:00:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And if I'm gonna do it, I just\Ngotta do it! Gotta! Gotta! That's me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.07,0:00:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Well, well, well, does\Neveryone have a lot of friends?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.56,0:00:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Friends you can have\Nfun with and laugh with.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.27,0:00:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sometime you have fights, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.70,0:00:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but you help each other\Neven during sad or rough times.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.21,0:00:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Precious friends like that. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.95,0:00:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm going to work hard with\Nthe help of Mia and Anna too!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.82,0:01:00.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm gonna! I'm gonna!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.05,0:01:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yaritai koto wa nani {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.65,0:01:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sou kikareru tabi {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.50,0:01:27.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Aoi sora miageta {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.29,0:01:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kotae wa only my heart {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.59,0:01:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Honto ni daiji na kotoba\Nwa kantan ni wa iwanai{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.12,0:01:46.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hikari ga yubisasu\Nbasho e to hashiridasu yo{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.16,0:01:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dakishimetai mono nara\Nnakitai hodo mune ni aru{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.32,0:02:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Egakitsuzukete yuku kitto take it someday{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.26,0:02:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shiroi kumo ga nagareru\Nchiheisen no mukou ni{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.31,0:02:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Naranderu mirai wa itsumo soba ni aru kara{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.49,0:02:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guiding you to a fantastic,\Nexciting, and intoxicating world,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.50,0:02:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaleido Stage's new production, Cinderella!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.17,0:02:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, the main cast members\Nare Layla Hamilton and Yuri Killian.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.65,0:02:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, we have\Nboldly included new members
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.67,0:02:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who joined our troupe this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.25,0:03:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to present a dramatic\Nstage with an unbelievable illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.01,0:03:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna got the role of the prince's attendant,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.49,0:03:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Mia won the role of the fairy godmother
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.98,0:03:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after she went through the final\Nselection process with several others.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.06,0:03:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could've been in it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.81,0:03:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you want to be in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.91,0:03:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.16,0:03:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! What? A child?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.34,0:03:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The audience should be all gone by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.75,0:03:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you're not allowed on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.65,0:03:33.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well... There are a lot\Nof circumstances behind this,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.32,0:03:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it's not exactly that I'm\N"not allowed on the stage"...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.50,0:03:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must be pretty bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.31,0:03:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you put it that way, you\Ncould say that I'm pretty bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.84,0:03:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know, everyone's\Nbad when they first start out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.04,0:03:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Even someone terrible can\Nget better if she works harder...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.05,0:03:46.20,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--What a loser.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.17,0:03:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, who was that kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.93,0:03:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Try Hard and You'll Get an Amazing Chance."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.86,0:04:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.02,0:04:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia's giving everything \Nshe's got again today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.34,0:04:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.81,0:04:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jump higher!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.41,0:04:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.87,0:04:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.54,0:04:25.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.48,0:04:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too low!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.07,0:04:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.99,0:04:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do it like you're drawing the\Naudience into your performance!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.81,0:04:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.69,0:04:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--They've been working since this\N morning without any breaks at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.71,0:04:32.86,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--Gracefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.86,0:04:33.66,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,--Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.65,0:04:36.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No breaks?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.71,0:04:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.14,0:04:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.33,0:04:51.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Layla!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.16,0:04:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like you are not very\Nmotivated. You can go home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.08,0:04:55.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. Please, one more time...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.83,0:04:59.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That won't be necessary.\NI'll find someone else more qualified.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.09,0:05:01.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or if that's not possible, I'll have\Nto have the production cancelled.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.81,0:05:02.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.35,0:05:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This scene is the climax\Nin the first half of the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.98,0:05:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this is how it's going to be,\Nwe're better off not doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.71,0:05:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.34,0:05:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll try harder! Please\Ngive me one more chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.86,0:05:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Layla!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.12,0:05:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.66,0:05:23.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or rather, she has way too little talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.69,0:05:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like, I might be the\Nonly one who can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.80,0:05:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if they're going to cancel the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.71,0:05:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that keeps up, they just might.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.75,0:05:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.77,0:05:43.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.70,0:05:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been doing this\Nevery morning without breaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.31,0:05:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.36,0:05:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot! If you keep this up, you'll get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.89,0:05:54.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have to. Because I can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.43,0:05:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you quit then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.39,0:06:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so third-rate to give\Nup for a reason like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.22,0:06:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a loser.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.23,0:06:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's her again!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.57,0:06:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know her?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.80,0:06:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Marion, don't interrupt \Ntheir practice! Marion!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.13,0:06:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.92,0:06:14.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.83,0:06:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.82,0:06:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.13,0:06:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Marion. She's the\Ndaughter of Jean, the sceneman.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.77,0:06:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's who she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.26,0:06:24.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, she went too far with what she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.30,0:06:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her mother used to be a star trampoliner.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.92,0:06:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She loves the trampoline, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.55,0:06:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's also talented, and people\Nused to have high expectations of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.84,0:06:37.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But after her mother died, \Nshe quit trampoline.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.52,0:06:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.22,0:06:42.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. She collapsed\Nsuddenly, and died soon after.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.09,0:06:45.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, Marion\Nbecame sarcastic like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.96,0:06:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.78,0:06:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But still, she said too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.44,0:06:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.92,0:06:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Mia.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.46,0:06:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay. Please leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.55,0:06:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.60,0:07:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia's grandma is hospitalized,\Nand her surgery date
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.20,0:07:05.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is the same day as the\Nopening day for Cinderella.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.80,0:07:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surgery? So Mia can't show her real abilities
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.62,0:07:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because she's worried\Nabout her grandma's surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.54,0:07:14.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really. It's more\Nlike she's trying too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.49,0:07:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.60,0:07:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her grandma is the one most\Nlooking forward to seeing Mia on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.33,0:07:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that when Mia \Nlearned she'd been cast,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.97,0:07:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she sent her grandma an e-mail\Nsaying that she would do her best,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.07,0:07:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so her grandma should do the same too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.47,0:07:30.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That's why she\Nwas pushing herself so hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.19,0:07:36.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mia has the tendency to lose\Nher cool when she tries too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.15,0:07:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Grandma.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.84,0:07:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I may not be able to keep my promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.48,0:07:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make the fairy godmother\Nrole a part for three people?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.74,0:07:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.76,0:07:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.93,0:07:53.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I think it sounds great!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.08,0:07:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't that make it even more difficult?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.00,0:07:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'd feel more reassured\Nif Anna and Sora were with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.16,0:07:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.98,0:08:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.19,0:08:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.30,0:08:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In short...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.72,0:08:04.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cast members would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.10,0:08:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the cast members\Nare Anna, Sora, and myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.80,0:08:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What{\i0}?! Me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.26,0:08:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. You don't want to?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.32,0:08:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I'm not saying that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.40,0:08:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.81,0:08:19.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm not sure if we can\Nget him to change the cast now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.73,0:08:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.20,0:08:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an interesting idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.77,0:08:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell the director about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.14,0:08:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure to come up with\Nsomething Layla will be satisfied with.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.63,0:08:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you mean you don't\Nmind me going on stage?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.73,0:08:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll decide that after I see the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.88,0:08:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the time limit is three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.09,0:08:42.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're not ready in three days,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.46,0:08:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will cancel Cinderella\Nas Layla suggested. Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.71,0:08:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir! We will do our best!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.28,0:09:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe Boss said okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.67,0:09:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since we've gotten this far,\Nwe have to be ready for the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.59,0:09:10.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm grateful to both of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.18,0:09:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm the one who should be grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.39,0:09:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.34,0:09:18.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.94,0:09:23.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have fun handing out toys\Nto kids in the audience now,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.19,0:09:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I still want to appear on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.97,0:09:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now, thanks to Mia,\Nmy wish may come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.61,0:09:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let the three of us join forces and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.73,0:09:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,appear on stage together!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.75,0:09:34.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.38,0:09:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, this is the climax
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.14,0:09:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and all of us jump towards \Nthe center like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.65,0:09:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.45,0:09:56.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if handing off wands while\Ndoing a cross jump is impossible after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.05,0:09:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.56,0:10:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia, why don't we change it\Ninto something more simple?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.24,0:10:05.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't, because we have to\Nconvince both Boss and Miss Layla.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.98,0:10:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could find a better idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.00,0:10:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you think of Cinderella...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.85,0:10:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Glass slippers! When you \Nthink of Cinderella...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.81,0:10:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A pumpkin prince!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.42,0:10:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no such thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.21,0:10:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.82,0:10:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.54,0:10:22.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.74,0:10:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.18,0:10:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A pumpkin prince?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.86,0:10:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! I'll take that role!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.82,0:10:28.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.77,0:10:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.70,0:10:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait; let me try the idea on the simulator.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.59,0:10:35.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll install some kind \Nof device in the wands.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.71,0:10:40.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we cross jump, we\Nspread out a big cloth like magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.78,0:10:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then make it look\Nlike a big pumpkin, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.89,0:10:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.12,0:10:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ooh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.47,0:10:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. A pumpkin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.65,0:10:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means if we don't fall at the\Nright moment together from the top,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.54,0:10:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it won't become the shape of a pumpkin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.97,0:10:57.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know. And once we\Nsuccessfully make the pumpkin,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.92,0:11:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cinderella will appear from inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.57,0:11:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing! It's like magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.56,0:11:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can make the audience\Nthink that, it'll really be magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.36,0:11:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A spell cast by the three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.00,0:11:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it needs a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.65,0:11:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about something like "Triple Illusion"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.98,0:11:14.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Triple Illusion?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.53,0:11:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, this maneuver's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.51,0:11:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.74,0:11:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, intensive training for\Nthe Triple Illusion begins tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.68,0:11:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do our best!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.80,0:11:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.48,0:11:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I have to work hard.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.59,0:11:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For Mia's sake and for myself.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.41,0:11:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is a long-awaited chance.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.62,0:11:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so flustered?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.09,0:11:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any normal person would be!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.70,0:11:44.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to tell you something. Lay down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.89,0:11:46.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.15,0:11:48.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I will talk to you like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.16,0:11:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.53,0:11:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will get right to the point. You\Nshould not pair up with those two girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.52,0:11:54.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.09,0:11:56.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your skill levels are far too disparate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.78,0:12:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.82,0:12:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that I suck, but this is my chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.80,0:12:06.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I did not mean it like that. Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.73,0:12:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please make sure to turn\Noff the light. Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.57,0:12:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reverse Star. A failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.14,0:12:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and turn off the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.81,0:12:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.79,0:12:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.24,0:12:43.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.93,0:12:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't keep blaming just yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.61,0:12:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just couldn't catch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.57,0:12:55.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.11,0:12:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just keep making mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.62,0:13:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.10,0:13:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We failed because our moves didn't match up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.87,0:13:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, it wasn't just your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.45,0:13:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Mia?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.73,0:13:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.71,0:13:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you think I shouldn't be part\Nof it, please feel free to say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.35,0:13:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.10,0:13:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.13,0:13:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My timing was also a little\Noff, so it could be my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.31,0:13:34.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my idea's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.48,0:13:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My idea was just impossible to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.67,0:13:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I thought, you're third-rate!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.20,0:13:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want people like\Nyou up on the trampoline!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.14,0:13:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moping around about whose\Nfault it was. You guys are losers!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.10,0:13:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter with you?\NThis has nothing to do with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.79,0:13:54.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It does too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.05,0:13:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because... Because...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.49,0:13:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the trampoline was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.27,0:14:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my mom's... my mom's favorite...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.60,0:14:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Marion...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.73,0:14:11.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Marion!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.64,0:14:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about the weird things Marion said.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.81,0:14:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please let me know whenever\Nyou need a trampoline adjustment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.08,0:14:25.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, let's practice, practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.36,0:14:28.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Layla...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.05,0:14:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.13,0:14:33.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think having three people\Nplay the fairy godmother
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.46,0:14:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will be a selling point \Nfor the upcoming show.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.40,0:14:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.85,0:14:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is why we need to make sure\Nit's perfect before the show starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.63,0:14:42.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we will do our best.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.34,0:14:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sora and Anna, please\Nstep down from this role.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.90,0:14:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.46,0:14:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect this routine using\Nyou, Charlotte, and Julie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.20,0:14:54.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the Triple Illusion is supposed\Nto be done by Sora, Anna, and myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.41,0:14:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are not doing this for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.37,0:15:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm only inviting you to be a part\Nof it because I heard this was your idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.08,0:15:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't like it,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.02,0:15:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will ask you to step down as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.99,0:15:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.66,0:15:11.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.19,0:15:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.13,0:15:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind. Please excuse us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.13,0:15:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's just the\Ndifference in talent, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.43,0:15:19.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like, sorry for being so talented.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.14,0:15:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.92,0:15:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.79,0:15:42.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.77,0:15:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're upset about what\NMarion said, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.93,0:15:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. I'm okay about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.43,0:15:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.95,0:15:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's kind of a long story, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.44,0:15:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.35,0:15:58.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the three of you were\Nworking so hard at it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.60,0:16:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, don't worry about it. It's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.59,0:16:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, where's Marion?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.59,0:16:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, she's probably hiding\Nsomewhere here in the lesson hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.06,0:16:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's always like that when she's sulking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.55,0:16:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well, she'll be back once she gets hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.49,0:16:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.42,0:16:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What is it?\N--About what Marion said earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.15,0:16:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.09,0:16:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it have something to\Ndo with the way she behaves?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.34,0:16:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is, if you don't mind,\Nwould you tell me about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.99,0:16:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you already heard\Nthat her mother passed away?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.27,0:16:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Six years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.13,0:16:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my wife, Cynthia, was a \Nstar at Kaleido Stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.47,0:16:41.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was an earnest\Nwoman who loved to practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.43,0:16:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There is no such thing as wasted practice.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.82,0:16:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We can be confident\Nbecause we practice every day.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.33,0:16:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Without that confidence, our\Nperformance wouldn't make anyone happy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.38,0:16:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But because she seldom took a break,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.59,0:16:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she might have made Marion lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.81,0:16:59.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then one day, Marion had a fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.11,0:17:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was unusual for her, but Marion\Nasked Cynthia not to go on stage that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.65,0:17:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But since there was no one\Nwho could substitute for Cynthia,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.35,0:17:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she went on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.71,0:17:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, on that particular day,\NCynthia made a big mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.53,0:17:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Mom, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.00,0:17:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was taken to the hospital right away,\Nbut her condition wasn't good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.05,0:17:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--It's because I was being so spoiled.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.45,0:17:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not your fault, Marion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.52,0:17:27.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was my mistake, so it's no one's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.48,0:17:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, Mom's going to recover\Nfrom these injuries really soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.78,0:17:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I'll show you even\Nmore amazing performances.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.38,0:17:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those were Cynthia's last words.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.34,0:17:40.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She passed away without ever\Nsetting foot on the stage again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.38,0:17:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since, in Marion's opinion,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.08,0:17:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,no trampoliner better\Nthan Cynthia has appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.36,0:17:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She can't be satisfied\Nwith anyone's performance,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.39,0:17:50.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and she's become sarcastic like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.51,0:17:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what happened.\NMarion must've really loved her mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.41,0:18:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And she must also love the Kaleido\NStage that her mom loved so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.09,0:18:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.86,0:18:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to thank you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.97,0:18:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad that I had a\Nchance to hear your story.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.20,0:18:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you think about it, it's weird\Nfor me to get depressed about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.70,0:18:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia's the one who gave me the\Npossibility of appearing on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.78,0:18:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, I made Mia feel bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.66,0:18:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I'd been able to do everything properly,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.50,0:18:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia wouldn't have had to be so torn.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.53,0:18:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll practice much harder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.16,0:19:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Marion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.86,0:19:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.47,0:19:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's been practicing\Nsince before the crack of dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.37,0:19:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mom used to do the same\Nbefore a new show opened, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.50,0:19:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.32,0:19:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.12,0:19:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.06,0:19:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Anna, good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.61,0:19:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't "good morning" me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.61,0:19:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're still the same reckless risk-taker.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.94,0:19:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.52,0:19:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is no time to be laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.40,0:19:50.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll practice with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.79,0:19:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.80,0:19:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are Charlotte and Julie?\NYou're not practicing with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.80,0:19:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I stepped down from the role.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.92,0:20:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.07,0:20:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you already told your grandma...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.22,0:20:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought about it, and I'd\Nrather perfect it with you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.77,0:20:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure my grandma would also\Nagree that's the better thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.94,0:20:11.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.30,0:20:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.40,0:20:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should have said so right away yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.29,0:20:17.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really sure about giving up on this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.79,0:20:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I haven't given up yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.46,0:20:21.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.31,0:20:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked them, "Please give us a\Nchance to show you our Triple Illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.44,0:20:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's still not good enough,\Nwe'll resign from our roles."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.17,0:20:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.67,0:20:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mia...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.58,0:20:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe they will become\Nfirst-rate Kaleido Stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.19,0:20:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.13,0:20:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, let's practice right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.85,0:20:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.75,0:20:43.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll try slowing down my spin a little,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.12,0:20:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so, Sora, can you try to speed up yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.11,0:20:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.32,0:20:49.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll throw in my\Norangutan pose in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.32,0:20:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.54,0:20:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have one day left. Let's work hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.90,0:20:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.93,0:20:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just now, Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.67,0:20:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.35,0:21:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.06,0:21:03.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's have breakfast.
